title: For Sale:  Super Nice Swiss K31 with Beautiful Figured Walnut Stock, All Matching
location: Apex, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent:
I have an all matching Swiss K31 in 7.5x55 Swiss for sale, it has minimal finish wear on the metal parts (honestly the finish is really great, it has some character so you know it's a surplus, but it's in such great shape that I know it had to have been a soldier bring back).  The stock is simply beautiful, it's has a really nice tiger stripe that has great luster, overall it's an exceptionally beautiful firearm.

K31s are simply the best of the Milsurp bolt actions.  They fire the 7.5x55 Swiss, which is very similar in power to a .308 Winchester.  GP11 rounds are common and can be found easily on sites like SGA in crates of 480 cartridges for around 50 cents a shot.  GP11 is a match-grade brass cased and non-corrosive round, and it was the round originally issued for these rifles.  Because of that, K31s tend to have great bores that do not have rust or pitting, which is the case with the rifle in this sale.  PPU also makes several loads of 7.5 Swiss including hunting cartridges, and Hornady makes an A-Max ballistic tip defense/hunting/match grade round as well.  The K31 feeds from a detachable 6 round box magazine and can be fed with stripper clips.

The K31 is a straight pull bolt action, so it's quicker to work than a Mosin or a Mauser.  You also have an extra round in the mag over both other rifles, and the gun locks open on an empty magazine.  This K31 shoots MOA and has a fantastic crisp two-state trigger.  

Price on the gun is 500$, I'm asking a premium because of the condition of the gun and the figure in the stock.  Simply put, it's the most beautiful figure in a K31 stock I've ever seen, and I collect these guns.  Also all of the parts match and they're in great condition.  K31s like this can go for 1500$+ with collectors, so honestly this is a steal.  

You'll need a NC DL, CCW prefered but not required, and you'll need to sign a bill of sale for FTF.  Willing to ship to an FFL of your choice on your dime.  It's 50 state legal to the best of my knowledge, so if you live in a commie state I can ship to you.

title: For Sale:  Zeiss Varipoint 1.1-4x24 Blaser iC ll Reticle 60...FREE SHIPPING...
postcontent: ZEISS 1.1-4 X 24 VARIPOINT WITH ILLUMINATION CONTROL. RETICLE (IC) #60, RAIL MOUNT NOT INCLUDED IN PRICE. R93 iC Illumination Control Blaser and Carl Zeiss revolutionise the operation of rifle and rifle scope Is the rifle cocked, then the illuminated reticle is on. With the iC concept from the two innovation leaders Blaser and Carl Zeiss this is always the case. Activating the illuminated reticle in crucial moments can no longer be forgotten. For the first time, rifle and rifle scope are synchronised in their functions. In the same moment the hunter cocks the R93, the illuminated reticle of his Varipoint rifle scope switches on. A small magnetic encoder in the cocking slide of the R93 iC is connected to a sensor on the underside of the Varipoint ocular thus activating the illuminated reticle. This results in a calmer approach to the moment before the shot is taken. The following situation is well known to many hunters on a driven hunt: when silently and unexpected a fox or wild boar comes into view, there is very little time to take the opportunity to shoot. The rifle is quickly mounted and aimed and then the shooter realises: the illuminated reticle is not on. Being irritated to such an extent, it is hardly possible to hit accurately. The same can also happen when hunting from a stand by night. With iC, events like this are a thing of the past: the hunter carefully mounts his rifle into the correct position, silently pushes the cocking slide forward and aims accurately thanks to the illuminated reticle which was automatically activated when cocking the rifle. The advantages of the iC concept are crystal clear: even when being under great pressure, forgetting to switch on the illuminated reticle cannot occur anymore. Through the cocking slide, the illuminated reticle is illuminated and remains illuminated as long as the rifle is cocked, no matter in which position the control button on the rifle scope is adjusted. Thanks to the ergonomically favourable position of the cocking slide of the R93 iC, the trigger hand remains on the pistol grip, whereas the leading hand must no longer be removed from the forearm to switch on the illuminated reticle on the scope. Shooter, rifle and scope are connected as one unit. The memory function which is integrated in the Varipoint iC ensures that the light intensity which has been adjusted last, is provided immediately. Independent from the position of the cocking slide, the light intensity is adjusted when the control button is pulled out and is saved when the button is pushed down. Every R93 can quickly be retrofitted with the iC at an affordable price. The Blaser dealer sends the bolt assembly to the Blaser factory where the iC cocking slide can be fitted. The premium line of riflescopes equipped with the most sophisticated ZEISS optics, state-of-the-art components, and highperformance features to meet the requirements of the most discriminating hunters and shooters. LotuTec® lens coating along with fully T* multicoating on all air-to-glass surfaces provides superior light transmission and optimum contrast, critical for twilight hunts. Large fields of view and precision adjustments get you on target quickly and accurately every time. The most versatile, high-performance optics with sophisticated illumination control for the perfect shot at any time of the day. The illuminated red dot is always clearly visible, in bright daylight as well as in extreme low light situations. When magnification is changed, the crosshair in the first image plane adjusts in size automatically, while the illuminated red dot reticle in the second image plane remains constant – so targets are never obscured, making Victory Varipoint rifle scopes the premium solution for fast and precise target acquisition and in excellent condition..

title: For Sale:  AK package, gun, scopes, magazines and ammunition
postcontent:
This is a Standard Draco pistol that I permanently attached an extended Krinkov style muzzle brake to bring it to just over 16". Get the NFA look, and performance, without the $200 registration. This gun surpasses all 922r requirements so you can use ANY magazine you want. It has a chrome lined bore for durability and corrosion resistance.

This gun is gassed PERFECTLY, has an amazing trigger and dead nuts reliable. Using Wolf 123 grain bullets the carrier stops about 1/4" from the trunion. This not only protects parts from damage it also results in a significant reduction in felt recoil. It does not throw brass into the next county like a typical over gassed AK.

Here are the modifications: 
TAPCO trigger that is adjustable for take up giving it a 3.5 pound trigger. It is better than any other AK trigger out there and better than most AR triggers.
Gas tube drilled to bleed off excessive gas to keep crud out of the receiver
Gas piston drilled to make sure it isn't over gassed 
Extra power recoil spring installed to reduce felt recoil
Side rail installed
ACE lightweight 9.5" stock, with 1" butt pad, installed (Folds to the right)
Stormwerkz hinge installed
US Palm grip installed
US made polymer forearm with molded in rail installed
Trigger group, bolt and carrier polished for reliability
Extended Krinkov style brake from CNC Warrior (I will include the cone that goes in the brake)
Sling loop made out of 550 cord installed

The "package" will include one 30 round magazine, one 75 round rear load drum (you can leave this one loaded), a Bushnell Trophy Red Dot with its own mount, a Tru Glo 1.5-6 scope with its own mount and 100 rounds of Wolf 123 grain FMJ. Both scopes are zeroed for 123 grain bullets at 100 yards as is the iron sight.

Gun has about 150 rounds through it to ensure reliability.

Package deal $1,100
Gun with one 30 round magazine $850

Honestly I would love to keep it but I enjoy building guns much more than owning or shooting them so I must sell it to fund the next project. This gun is a fun gun to shoot and is SUPER easy to bump fire with the trigger. Bursts or mag dumps are no problem with this gun.

Feel free to ask ANY questions.
